# Security Rules

## Secrets Management

- NEVER commit API keys, tokens, passwords, or secrets to git
- Use environment variables or 1Password CLI (`op run`)
- If you see a secret in code: flag it immediately, do not proceed

## Input Validation

- Validate ALL external inputs with Zod before processing
- Sanitize user inputs before database queries
- Use parameterized queries; no string interpolation in SQL

## Dependencies

- Keep dependencies up to date (Dependabot handles this)
- Review new dependencies for supply chain risks
- Pin GitHub Action versions to SHA hashes (not tags)

## API Security

- Minimum required scopes for all API tokens
- Rotate tokens on suspected compromise
- Log access patterns for sensitive operations

## Code Review

- Security-sensitive changes need explicit review
- CODEOWNERS enforces reviewer requirements
- No force-push to protected branches
